  "text": "Note that while the recovery rates are very similar, the heat maps showing the corresponding spectral gaps differ significantly. Therefore, for the random Erdős-Rényi graph model, the lack of a large spectral gap in the former case does not lead to an erroneous solution, and we are still able to recover the rank-one structure. However, we refer the reader to Section 3.2 in [CITATION_1] , for a detailed explanation of the additional noise robustness the above normalization brings for the case of large degree nodes in the graph, and its connection to the normalized discrete graph Laplacian. ",
